## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[User Search] --> B{AmazonCache < 6hrs?}
    B -->|Yes| D[Cached Products]
    B -->|No| C[Scrape Best Sellers]
    C --> D
    C -->|Fail| E["generateProducts() fallback"]
    D --> F[Google Trends overlay]
    F --> G[gradeProduct]
    G --> H[Return to frontend]
    E --> F
```

## Key Design Decisions
- **Best Sellers pages** (not search results) — more stable, less likely to get blocked
- **6-hour MongoDB cache** — reduces Amazon requests dramatically
- **Keyword filtering** — scrapes category page, filters by relevance
- **Fallback guaranteed** — if Amazon fails, [generateProducts()](file:///c:/Users/dasar/DropGravity%20Pro/server/engine/productGenerator.js#365-412) runs automatically
- **`dataSource: 'amazon'`** — ready for future multi-source architecture
